P21 (149-160) and its derivatives were tested for ability to inhibit CDK1/cyclin B kinase activity in phosphorylating histone H1 or GST-pRb (Table 2).
None of the tested peptides were able to inhibit significantly the CDK1/cyclin B-induced phosphorylation of GST-pRb and only the highest peptide concentrations used (200 μM) had a marginal inhibitory effect on CDK1/cyclin B kinase activity.

The IC 50 of the most active peptide—p21 (149-160) 153A for CDK2-Cyclin E induced phosphorylation of GST-Rb was 40 nM which is approximately 50 fold higher than the IC 50 value for p21<sup>WAF1</sup>.
